Okay, so everyone should be able to join their rooms.

312
00:39:30,111 --> 00:39:31,752
And Doug, you can stop your screen share.

313
00:39:33,962 --> 00:39:38,379
I'll leave this up momentarily so that folks see the in case I need to review the.

314
00:41:11,749 --> 00:41:12,290
Hi, everyone.

315
00:41:12,330 --> 00:41:15,074
This is Melissa Dulé from the MBTA.

316
00:41:15,435 --> 00:41:16,977
We'll just give another minute.

317
00:41:17,338 --> 00:41:22,847
I see folks are still signing themselves to this particular breakout room.

318
00:41:23,208 --> 00:41:26,533
So we'll start shortly.

319
00:42:03,403 --> 00:42:05,485
This is breakout room number two.

320
00:42:06,445 --> 00:42:13,430
We will be covering root changes in Arlington, Bedford, Burlington, Cambridge, Lexington, Lincoln, Medford, Somerville, Winchester, and Woburn.

321
00:42:41,578 --> 00:42:42,280
Let's get started.

322
00:42:44,124 --> 00:42:48,033
My name is Melissa Dulé, and I'm the Senior Director of Service Planning.

323
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:57,762
I'll be walking through the changes that we made to the draft bus network redesign map.

324
00:42:58,522 --> 00:43:05,244
As Doug mentioned in the first part of the presentation, we made meaningful changes to the network map based on the feedback that we received.

325
00:43:06,124 --> 00:43:16,108
A note about order, I'm largely going to present these in numeric order, but there are some routes that are interrelated, so occasionally I may go out of order when there are related route changes.

326
00:43:17,783 --> 00:43:23,809
We made a number of changes, restoring existing routes in whole or in part.

327
00:43:24,349 --> 00:43:29,694
I've shown a subset of the routes that we'll be covering today here.

328
00:43:29,834 --> 00:43:33,418
So this is a little bit different than the slide that Doug showed earlier.

329
00:43:34,198 --> 00:43:44,824
Sometimes we've made route changes to better serve medical facilities or senior housing or other destinations at the request of municipalities and others.

330
00:43:45,624 --> 00:43:48,506
Sometimes we've added new routes back into the proposed.

331
00:43:59,052 --> 00:44:03,114
Sometimes we've made frequency or span adjustments.

332
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:20,877
So the first batch of routes that I'll be talking about relates to the initial proposal for the T39, but that also affects T47 and T96.

333
00:44:20,957 --> 00:44:25,363
So the next slides I'll present together.

334
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:41,295
The former proposal was to connect the T39 from Jamaica Plain to Longwood Medical, Boston University, Cambridge, and Somerville, ultimately ending at Porter Square in Cambridge.

335
00:44:42,135 --> 00:44:44,476
But we heard that the route was too long.

336
00:44:45,177 --> 00:45:00,104
This is something that we'd heard from the public, from elected officials, and even during our operator in-reach events, we'd heard that our bus operators were concerned with the route's length and the availability of restroom access for such a long route.

337
00:45:01,224 --> 00:45:07,707
Also, some of the other things that we'd heard, Jamaica Plain in particular, wanted direct service to Copley.

338
00:45:08,468 --> 00:45:13,370
And there is the history there with the former Arborway Greenline service providing that direct connection.

339
00:45:13,450 --> 00:45:14,871
So that was important to maintain.

340
00:45:17,312 --> 00:45:26,777
In Cambridge, the city was concerned with the ability to carve out layover space at Porter Square, given some of the protected bike infrastructure that has gone in.

341
00:45:28,478 --> 00:45:41,227
Summerville residents had noted that there was no direct connection between Davis Square and Union Square that had required a transfer between the T-96 and the T-39 in our original proposal.

342
00:45:41,487 --> 00:45:46,070
So synthesizing all this different feedback that we'd received on many different aspects,

343
00:45:47,915 --> 00:45:50,357
We end up with the revised proposal as shown.

344
00:45:51,758 --> 00:46:04,850
The T39 on the left side would retain its direct service to Copley like it does now, and this would replace our initial proposal that had gone all the way up through Cambridge into Union Square and Porter Square.

345
00:46:05,856 --> 00:46:20,630
On the left, you can see that we're proposing we would get that connectivity between Union Square and Cambridge, Cambridge Port, Boston University, and Ruggles with a new route, T47.

346
00:46:20,730 --> 00:46:25,494
So this is similar to today's 47 bus, but the route is a little different.

347
00:46:25,914 --> 00:46:29,498
So this would start actually a little bit beyond Union Square.

348
00:46:30,558 --> 00:46:36,784
near the future East Somerville station that will be opening on the Green Line extension later this year.

349
00:46:37,865 --> 00:46:39,506
And it would only go as far as Ruggles.

350
00:46:39,626 --> 00:46:46,852
We have other services that would serve Broadway station and Albany Street and other portions of today's Route 47.

351
00:46:47,112 --> 00:46:51,256
And this would be a T47 route, meaning that it would be a high frequency service.

352
00:46:51,716 --> 00:46:55,199
It would be every 15 minutes or better, seven days a week from 5 a.m.

353
00:46:55,219 --> 00:46:55,519
to 1 a.m.

354
00:46:59,422 --> 00:47:21,800
And that gets the connectivity that we were really looking for, getting folks in Cambridge and Somerville to job opportunities at the Longwood Medical Area, to opportunities for patient care, and also to the BU area, while still allowing that transfer to the T39 for folks who are interested in continuing out to Jamaica Plain and Forest Hills.

355
00:47:23,702 --> 00:47:27,144
On the next slide, I can show you how we also made some changes to T96.

356
00:47:29,983 --> 00:47:42,810
I had mentioned one of the things that we'd heard from Somerville in particular was interest in extending a one-seat ride with high frequency between Davis Square and Union Square, two very important squares within Somerville.

357
00:47:43,231 --> 00:47:53,997
So by sliding where the T39 and the T96 connect, except now that it's the T47, we slid that connection point to Union Square.

358
00:47:54,757 --> 00:48:02,401
So what that means is that there would now be high frequency service directly between Davis and Union on the new T96.

359
00:48:03,501 --> 00:48:07,363
So this relates to the changes to the T39 that I had mentioned.

360
00:48:07,743 --> 00:48:14,706
But at the same time, we also have another different unrelated route change on the Medford portion of the T96 as well.

361
00:48:16,828 --> 00:48:30,853
We heard from many riders of the T96 along Winthrop Street, that would be over here, and George Street on the former proposal to keep service on College Ave, that would create a hardship for them.

362
00:48:31,413 --> 00:48:37,655
The walk out to College Ave was just too far, this is College Ave over here, for the volume of riders there.

363
00:48:38,056 --> 00:48:44,718
In the revised proposal, the T96 would serve High Street, from Medford Square to Winthrop Circle,

364
00:48:46,513 --> 00:49:08,898
and would travel down Winthrop Street to George Street, meaning that we're able to provide direct high-frequency service to some existing Route 94 riders along High Street here, and also to cut down that walk distance for the folks who had written us coming from George Street or folks coming from Winthrop Street in the Medgar Hillside area.

365
00:49:14,580 --> 00:49:18,221
The next package of changes relates to bus route 55.

366
00:49:20,241 --> 00:49:41,107
The 55 had been proposed as a combination of today's CT2 and 55 and provided local connectivity to the West Fens neighborhood via transfer at a future accessible Heinz station, while also connecting Kendall Square and the Red Line to the Longwood Medical Area.

367
00:49:42,319 --> 00:49:48,245
But we heard from residents in the West Fens, including many seniors, that they really valued that direct connection to Copley Square.

368
00:49:48,746 --> 00:49:58,195
So we've split apart our proposal into the 55 to Copley with an 85 bus that serves the function of the CT2 for Kendall and Longwood trips.

369
00:49:58,936 --> 00:50:03,561
We're retiring the CT2 nomenclature and instead using the 85 numbers in its place.

370
00:50:05,565 --> 00:50:10,672
have another map that shows a little bit more of the 85 also.

371
00:50:11,273 --> 00:50:17,342
So we would continue to serve Kendall Square, the Port neighborhood in Cambridge, Union Square,

372
00:50:19,096 --> 00:50:40,347
And instead of Avon Street in Spring Hill, like the 85 uses today to turn around, due to planned roadway changes in Somerville, we would instead provide a north-south connection between Union Square and Assembly, which is something that we'd heard requested multiple times during our outreach earlier this summer.

373
00:50:47,770 --> 00:50:50,592
Next we have Route 64.

374
00:50:53,094 --> 00:51:04,642
As in our original proposal, we're looking to extend the route to Kendall Square on all days of the week so that there would be a consistent service pattern, unlike today's service, which only goes to Kendall on weekdays.

375
00:51:05,602 --> 00:51:13,088
And we also have two changes on the Boston end of the route to maintain service to North Beacon Street due to significant development plans.

376
00:51:14,208 --> 00:51:22,791
And also to not show that the route would serve future West Station, which is slated to open after our five-year implementation window.

377
00:51:23,831 --> 00:51:26,612
It currently looks like West Station is slated for about 10 years out.

378
00:51:27,192 --> 00:51:36,035
So we're continuing to show, at least for the short term, that the 64 would do what it does today on this stretch through Austin.

379
00:51:41,412 --> 00:51:43,113
Next we have route 74.

380
00:51:43,574 --> 00:51:51,380
This is probably one of the biggest concerns that we had heard within Cambridge was the loss of frequency on Concord Ave.

381
00:51:51,980 --> 00:51:56,824
We did not have the route 74 on the initial map, which only had the routes 75 and 78.

382
00:51:59,306 --> 00:52:15,219
But with the amount of development slated for the area, including low income housing, which is expected to attract significant transit trips, and also the existing residential employment and retail opportunities along Concord Ave and near Fresh Pond Circle, we've added the Route 74 back in.

383
00:52:17,561 --> 00:52:25,888
This would also have new Sunday service compared to today's service because the 74 only operates Mondays through Saturdays.

384
00:52:27,839 --> 00:52:33,461
At the Belmont end of the route, we also are showing a small route change.

385
00:52:34,121 --> 00:52:37,882
We're showing the route continuing to Belmont Center under the railroad bridge.

386
00:52:38,582 --> 00:52:52,026
This would not be possible now with the posted low clearance, but we have some ideas for intersection changes that would allow the posted bridge height to be revised in a way that would allow for restored bus service under the bridge and into Belmont Center.

387
00:52:56,489 --> 00:52:58,410
Next, we have Route 76.

388
00:53:00,330 --> 00:53:23,358
One concern we'd heard about this route, which goes out to the Hanscom Civil Air Terminal in Bedford and to Lincoln Lab and through Lexington and into ALF, was that we had proposed only operating peak period service, and we'd instead

389
00:53:24,078 --> 00:53:34,966
upgraded the sort of companion Route 62 to be a seven-day service, but that was something that was causing a hardship that we'd heard about during our initial outreach.

390
00:53:35,186 --> 00:53:43,653
So we have restored midday service on the Route 76 while still having the 62 upgraded to seven-day service.

391
00:53:44,633 --> 00:53:53,120
We also heard about concern about the lack of service along Acorn Park Drive in Cambridge off of Route 2, which is served by today's inbound route.

392
00:53:55,359 --> 00:54:04,943
This serves a number of office parks and other developments, and we have added that Acorn Park Drive portion of the route back into both the routes 62 and the 76.

393
00:54:09,818 --> 00:54:17,501
There was also a concern from Lincoln Lab riders that they were being forced to take a longer trip via the Hanscom Civil Air terminal for their connections.

394
00:54:18,362 --> 00:54:30,647
The intention is that we would serve Lincoln Lab and Hanscom only once per round trip, like we do today, and that we would go outbound in the mornings to Lincoln Lab first, then inbound from Hanscom, and then reverse that for the PM.

395
00:54:30,807 --> 00:54:39,311
That gives the most direct trips to the most number of riders without folks having to kind of take a lengthy detour through the other portion of the route.

396
00:54:40,602 --> 00:55:02,061
And then lastly, there was a concern in Lexington about the loss of service to Lexington Center, which provides either better frequency to the portion of the route where it overlaps with the 62, or also serves a small stretch over near the high school, just to the west of Mass Ave.

397
00:55:04,283 --> 00:55:06,165
By rerouting the 62 on a

398
00:55:08,528 --> 00:55:29,693
slightly longer routing, we're able to serve Lexington Center, get better frequency to that important town center in Lexington, allow for transfer opportunities to the Lexpress routes that the town of Lexington operates, and get that connection to the high school that folks are looking for.

399
00:55:30,173 --> 00:55:31,674
So those are the changes to Route 76.

400
00:55:36,346 --> 00:55:37,987
Next we have Route 80.

401
00:55:39,087 --> 00:55:47,852
One of the pieces that we had heard that was missing from our original map proposal was a connection from Arlington to the Medford Greenline Extension Bridge.

402
00:55:48,668 --> 00:55:58,533
In the original proposal, we had not included Route 80 at all due to substantial overlaps between Route 80 and the Medford-Tufts branch of the Green Line that's slated to open later this year.

403
00:55:59,573 --> 00:56:11,879
In the revised proposal, we restore the Route 80 connection from Arlington Center, here, to Boston Ave and Medford-Tufts Green Line Extension Station.

404
00:56:12,019 --> 00:56:15,701
And from there, we continue to Davis Square for our Red Line connection.

405
00:56:16,924 --> 00:56:30,116
This also becomes the primary Boston Ave connection here in Medford, which replaces the proposed 94 that had formerly been on Boston Ave in our initial proposal, and which I have a slide on later.

406
00:56:32,799 --> 00:56:34,100
At the outer end of the Route 80,

407
00:56:36,165 --> 00:56:42,308
We continue the route from Arlington Center out to Burlington, like the 350 bus does today.

408
00:56:43,089 --> 00:57:01,178
So the proposed network redesign version of Route 80 would also be a Route 350 replacement to Burlington Mall Road, 3rd Ave, and North Burlington, and would have both Green Line and Red Line connections at Medford Tufts and at Davis Station.

409
00:57:05,156 --> 00:57:06,997
Next we have route 83.

410
00:57:08,597 --> 00:57:18,501
On the left is our original proposal, which had been to extend the service to Kendall Square, which would have connected Rinjav, Inman Square, and the Port neighborhood to Kendall.

411
00:57:19,262 --> 00:57:31,147
But we heard from Cambridge staff and residents on the importance of the bus connection, specifically from Rinjav users, to the services and resources in Central Square, where the 83 terminates today.

412
00:57:32,107 --> 00:57:41,450
With other route improvements slated for Kendall Square, we felt that we could continue to route the 83 at Central without impacting the greater vision for improved connectivity to Kendall Square.

413
00:57:47,092 --> 00:57:52,053
So you can see on the right, we're preserving the 83 to Central Square in the new network.

414
00:57:56,934 --> 00:57:57,555
Next, we have route 87.

415
00:57:59,862 --> 00:58:12,805
We had formally proposed significant changes to Route 87, including tying together Broadway and Clarendon Hill with Harvard Street in Medford and Mystic Ave in Medford and Somerville.

416
00:58:13,486 --> 00:58:17,687
You can see the original proposal on the left, which is very different from today's 87 bus.

417
00:58:20,460 --> 00:58:38,257
One of the biggest concerns, and we heard many, many concerns from Somerville and Cambridge and Medford, was about the lack of direct service between Clarendon Hill, Davis, Union Square, Market Basket, Twin City Plaza, and Lechmere.

418
00:58:38,557 --> 00:58:41,620
And we heard a lot, lot, lot of comments on this.

419
00:58:42,301 --> 00:58:51,023
So in this proposal, we have restored the Route 87 as a direct route that travels from Arlington Center to Lechmere Station.

420
00:58:51,423 --> 00:59:01,126
And like in the proposal, the route would operate a consistent service pattern seven days a week, unlike today's route that only goes as far as Clarendon Hill on Sundays.

421
00:59:01,246 --> 00:59:07,888
So we would be having the 87 go to Arlington Center on Sundays, which is different from today's 87.

422
00:59:09,673 --> 00:59:23,259
This does mean that there would be a stretch of Harvard Street in Medford where we had proposed running new service and where we would not have service in the revised version of the network.

423
00:59:24,239 --> 00:59:33,803
Also, it means that Mystic Ave in Medford would be served via the Route 95, which I will talk about shortly.

424
00:59:41,759 --> 00:59:55,472
As part of the original 87 proposal, we had also had it be a combination with today's 67 bus to serve the Turkey Hill neighborhood in Arlington, as shown on the left.

425
00:59:56,213 --> 01:00:03,260
We received a significant amount of feedback from Turkey Hill that having a red line connection at Alewife specifically was important.

426
01:00:04,551 --> 01:00:18,019
We also heard from our operator in-reach efforts that the proposed route length from Turkey Hill to Sullivan was too long, especially since there are not good restroom facilities at the Turkey Hill end of the line, which is in a quiet residential neighborhood.

427
01:00:18,839 --> 01:00:28,905
This proposal spins off the 67 back onto a separate route, which would operate Turkey Hill to Alewife weekdays only, as shown on the right.

428
01:00:30,238 --> 01:00:46,761
There is a route change from today's 67 and that the bus would stay on Mass Ave from Arlington Center to Alewife Brook Parkway as a replacement for the 350 connections on this stretch into Alewife due to the 350 replacement with the 80 via Boston Ave that I spoke about earlier.

429
01:00:47,702 --> 01:00:54,583
This would omit Pleasant Street and Route 2, but those areas would still have other transit service under this proposal.

430
01:01:00,585 --> 01:01:01,925
Next, group 89.

431
01:01:03,986 --> 01:01:10,328
This is probably the other biggest issue that we had heard in Somerville and Medford.

432
01:01:11,348 --> 01:01:18,070
It was the lack of connection in our original map between Winter Hill, Ball Square, and Davis Square.

433
01:01:18,330 --> 01:01:26,392
On the left, you can see our original proposal, which included upgraded high frequency service on the T101 along Broadway at Goon Square,

434
01:01:26,992 --> 01:01:36,194
the new Green Line extension at Ball Square, and a high-frequency T96 service on College Ave, but there was not a direct connection between Winter Hill and Davis.

435
01:01:37,074 --> 01:01:53,818
In the new map on the right, you can see the proposed Route 89, which would operate consistently with a single service pattern between Davis and Sullivan, with a stop near the new Ball Square station on the Green Line extension that should be opening later this year.

436
01:01:54,538 --> 01:02:02,785
For Route 89 users, note that there would not be a mix of some Clarendon Hill trips and some Davis trips like there is today.

437
01:02:03,686 --> 01:02:10,072
For connections to Clarendon Hill, please use the 87 or the 90 and connect at Davis to this 89 service.

438
01:02:12,868 --> 01:02:30,623
Now, as a result of the 89 restoration, we have also put the T-101 back onto Main Street in Medford, like it does today, which serves a little farther north on the Medford side of Winter Hill, while the 89 will still serve Magoon Square on Broadway.

439
01:02:32,305 --> 01:02:36,768
So you can see on the map on the right, the 101, T-101 kind of

440
01:02:38,790 --> 01:02:47,757
takes this soft corner here on Main Street and omits Magoon Square, unlike the older version which had been squared off a little bit.

441
01:02:48,457 --> 01:02:50,058
I say squared off, that's not really a square.

442
01:02:55,102 --> 01:02:56,924
Next, Route 90

443
01:02:59,662 --> 01:03:11,769
In response to concerns with reliability and route length, both from riders and also from our operator in-reach efforts, we've looked at shortening this route for better reliability.

444
01:03:11,809 --> 01:03:17,732
At the western end, this would not go to Arlington Center, but rather would terminate at Clarendon Hill.

445
01:03:18,812 --> 01:03:22,975
Broadway and Arlington would still be served by seven-day service on the Route 87 bus.

446
01:03:24,830 --> 01:03:31,274
On the eastern end, this would not go to Chelsea and Everett directly, but would terminate at Assembly Station.

447
01:03:33,056 --> 01:03:49,347
This is different from today's route in that we omit the Sullivan Station connections directly and instead provide an orange line connection on Revolution Drive at Assembly Station, much closer to the orange line than today's stop that's on Grand Union Boulevard.

448
01:03:50,592 --> 01:03:58,735
We also have a separate connection from Assembly to Chelsea and Everett as Route 113 that I'll get into shortly.

449
01:03:59,515 --> 01:04:09,178
Now also in response to concerns about the difficulty of connections between Route 90 and the Green Line, especially since this route is intended to be a Route 88 replacement,

450
01:04:09,918 --> 01:04:29,213
And especially since Gilman Station on the Green Line Extension right behind City Hall and the high school is surrounded with steep grades, there was also a small reroute onto Tufts Street and Washington Street to help facilitate better transfer opportunities at East Somerville Station on the Green Line Extension.

451
01:04:29,833 --> 01:04:38,880
This requires some street crossings, but we hope this can make a better transfer option available, especially in winter months when steep grades can be most challenging.

452
01:04:40,720 --> 01:04:50,607
And then there were also several comments, more than several, many, many comments received on the original proposal regarding the loss of service frequency along Highland Ave overall.

453
01:04:51,568 --> 01:04:56,471
We looked at some of our hours calculations and this criticism was absolutely fair and not our intention.

454
01:04:56,992 --> 01:05:04,977
So as a result, this service has been upgraded to every 20-minute service, mostly seven days per week, with some periods of every 30-minute service after 10 p.m.

455
01:05:06,178 --> 01:05:12,368
Lastly, I do want to highlight that this service is intended to be a combination of the route 88 and 90.

456
01:05:12,929 --> 01:05:16,775
So the service would become a more significant route than the 90 is today.

457
01:05:16,795 --> 01:05:21,462
It would still serve Clarendon Hill, as it had done in our original proposal.

458
01:05:24,028 --> 01:05:38,666
And it would still serve those important school related trips that students and caregivers from all over Somerville might be making to get from West Somerville and Davis and Spring Hill to the high school or to the East Somerville Community School or to the Capuano.

459
01:05:39,347 --> 01:05:48,056
Also, the simplified schedules that were published on the trip planner, do not include any of those special trips that may be needed that might operate today.

460
01:05:48,136 --> 01:05:56,525
For example, today there are some afternoon trips on Route 88 that start at the high school during Somerville High School on Highland Ave.

461
01:05:57,505 --> 01:06:03,729
during periods when large crowds of students might overwhelm the regular 88 service traveling through.

462
01:06:03,829 --> 01:06:09,813
So our expectation is that these trips could still operate, but that they would become 90 trips instead of 88 trips.

463
01:06:16,289 --> 01:06:22,431
And I had mentioned as part of the Route 90 shortening that we created the new Route 113.

464
01:06:22,911 --> 01:06:31,174
So it's been spun off into a separate route that would connect Assembly to Sullivan and over to Everett and Chelsea.

465
01:06:32,291 --> 01:06:37,994
This gets better connectivity between Chelsea, Everett, and Somerville, as had been suggested in our original proposal.

466
01:06:38,874 --> 01:06:52,920
And this has been extended to Bellingham Square in Chelsea, which was something we'd heard requested in our Chelsea focus groups, as the initial 90 proposal had only gone as far as Chelsea Station and the Market Basket.

467
01:06:58,202 --> 01:06:59,123
Next we have

468
01:07:00,000 --> 01:07:02,421
the routes 94 and 134.

469
01:07:04,341 --> 01:07:16,165
So 94 formerly had been proposed as shown on the left to serve Boston Ave, West Medford, Playstead Road, Winchester, Woburn, and Burlington.

470
01:07:17,685 --> 01:07:21,166
And in the new proposal, there is no route 94.

471
01:07:21,866 --> 01:07:26,768
So instead, we propose restoring the route 134 from North Woburn

472
01:07:27,728 --> 01:07:32,169
to Winchester, Medford and Wellington, along with some changes to the 80 and 354.

473
01:07:33,110 --> 01:07:34,410
Now there's a few reasons for this.

474
01:07:35,370 --> 01:07:46,454
One, there was a problem with the original route 94 and that the bus was not able to make one of the turns near West Medford station due to the railroad crossing and some of the intersection geometry.

475
01:07:47,770 --> 01:07:54,415
We also had a lot of interest in restoring the Route 354 express route in Burlington, Woburn, and Medford.

476
01:07:54,715 --> 01:08:03,361
But that led to some other network changes, including ultimately the elimination of Route 133 out to Anderson, Woburn as a resource offset.

477
01:08:03,441 --> 01:08:04,282
And I'll talk about that.

478
01:08:04,302 --> 01:08:05,303
I have another slide later.

479
01:08:06,223 --> 01:08:12,128
And then there's also the extension of Route 80 to Burlington that I spoke about on an earlier slide.

480
01:08:12,828 --> 01:08:20,394
So with all these changes, nearly all of the proposed 94 is covered by the new 80, 134, and 354.

481
01:08:20,734 --> 01:08:27,520
However, the one change that I do want to highlight is that Placestead Road, which is right about

482
01:08:27,980 --> 01:08:35,887
there in West Medford would not have direct service that had been served in our earlier version of the network.

483
01:08:36,607 --> 01:08:44,333
That stretch of Placedead Road is entirely within half a mile of other bus service on High Street or Winthrop Street or the commuter rail station also.

484
01:08:45,434 --> 01:08:57,597
Also, the proposed 134 would be a little different than today's 134 in that it's proposed to go down Locust Street in Medford, which is that little street right next to the Wegmans.

485
01:08:58,558 --> 01:09:07,720
And then it would also have a more consistent service pattern with more full trips and fewer of those short, weird trips that run on nights and weekends that only go to Medford Square. 95.

486
01:09:16,120 --> 01:09:22,685
Formerly, our proposal on the 95, shown on the left, would go to Wellington.

487
01:09:23,365 --> 01:09:34,234
The revised version on the right goes via Mystic Ave and serves part of Medford that are poised for substantial redevelopment, and is similar to what most 95 trips do today.

488
01:09:34,794 --> 01:09:41,158
This also fills in for the route 87 that I spoke about earlier, which has been restored to leech mirror and the revised map.

489
01:09:41,198 --> 01:09:50,104
So the 95 is filling that void on Mystic Ave that was left behind by shifting the 87 back to its current alignment.

490
01:09:50,824 --> 01:10:04,233
So compared to today's 95, there would be one consistent service pattern, in that the route would go from Arlington to Sullivan consistently, rather than the current service pattern where some trips start in Arlington and some trips start on Placetip Road.

491
01:10:05,273 --> 01:10:13,498
Also, the frequency of this route is slated to improve to every 20 minutes, mostly, seven days a week, with perhaps some 30-minute service after 10 p.m.

492
01:10:14,639 --> 01:10:23,806
This fills in a gap in between the three high frequency corridors that were newly proposed in Medford as part of the bus network redesign process.

493
01:10:25,287 --> 01:10:31,232
So that gives more prominence to this Route 95 in Medford.

494
01:10:34,155 --> 01:10:36,636
Also in Medford, we have some changes to the Route 99 and 108.

495
01:10:39,322 --> 01:10:48,266
Bus route 99 was proposed as shown on the left most map, and would serve Middlesex Ave and Medford and Wellington station.

496
01:10:49,006 --> 01:10:52,847
Now based on feedback we heard regarding loss of service to commercial street.

497
01:10:54,866 --> 01:11:07,276
think that's actually Malden near the super 88 and Medford Street near some medical facilities like the Cambridge Health Alliance and also other locations in Everett from current 97 riders.

498
01:11:07,616 --> 01:11:13,081
We've extended the 99 in the center map like a 97 through Everett

499
01:11:15,021 --> 01:11:19,664
to the Broadway and to the Gateway Center and on to Wellington.

500
01:11:20,444 --> 01:11:31,770
The Middlesex Ave portion of the route would still be served by the extended 108 as shown on the right which had formerly been proposed to terminate at Malden.

501
01:11:32,431 --> 01:11:43,237
So in this case what we ended up with is there's net one more route kind of between Malden Center and Wellington so that we could fill in some gaps that had been

502
01:11:43,938 --> 01:11:55,313
left in the initial version of the network, but there's no sections that we're discontinuing globally as part of this package of changes here.

503
01:12:00,280 --> 01:12:00,640
Bus route 100.

504
01:12:02,597 --> 01:12:16,048
This had been proposed to continue via the current terminus near Elm Street across to Governors Ave and then up Winthrop Street to Medford High School and out this way.

505
01:12:16,989 --> 01:12:28,518
We propose that the 100 should terminate as it does today near Elm Street because we've restored the 134 service on Winthrop Ave through Medford Square and over to Wellington.

506
01:12:29,158 --> 01:12:33,228
Though this does mean that there would be no service on Governor's Ave.

507
01:12:33,609 --> 01:12:38,119
When we did have bus service operating there, it was very, very low ridership.

508
01:12:42,501 --> 01:12:43,601
Only a couple more slides.

509
01:12:45,522 --> 01:12:48,583
We have some changes, bus routes 133 and 131.

510
01:12:50,864 --> 01:12:53,485
The 133 initial proposed route is on the left.

511
01:12:54,485 --> 01:12:58,387
In the new network, there is no route 133, but we've modified our proposed 131.

512
01:12:59,367 --> 01:13:00,867
provide much of the functionality.

513
01:13:01,247 --> 01:13:17,271
So the 133 initially had included new service to Anderson-Woburn commuter rail, and had been part of a package of changes to create local bus service instead of the express services in Burlington and Woburn, and new connections to Stona, Melrose, and the Orange Line.

514
01:13:17,611 --> 01:13:25,012
However, with the restoration of the 354 express route, one of the trade-offs was that we had to truncate some new service extensions.

515
01:13:25,112 --> 01:13:28,813
So you can see that we're no longer showing bus service to Anderson-Woburn.

516
01:13:30,033 --> 01:13:40,319
The North Woburn service will be part of the 134 route that I spoke about previously, and the local Woburn, Stoneham, and Melrose connection will be part of the route 131.

517
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:44,942
Oh, thank goodness.

518
01:13:45,442 --> 01:13:46,243
I have a little more time.

519
01:13:52,012 --> 01:14:04,576
So as part of the route network changes, we also removed part of the proposed extension of Route 131 out to Saugus and Lynn, but most of this is picked up with the modified 429.

520
01:14:05,136 --> 01:14:10,058
That's primarily outside of our service area, so I won't go into too much detail there.

521
01:14:11,365 --> 01:14:18,332
So going back to the $350,000, we talked about this briefly when I mentioned the $80,000 earlier.

522
01:14:19,192 --> 01:14:30,523
One thing that the proposed $80,000 does differently than the initial proposed $350,000 on the left is that we would continue to serve Burlington Mall Road and 3rd Avenue

523
01:14:32,305 --> 01:14:46,292
directly, the original proposal had separated out the Burlington Mall Road portion of the route onto a separate 94 to make the 350 more direct and thus have shorter, more competitive travel times as part of the 354 express bus elimination.

524
01:14:47,012 --> 01:14:59,818
But with the preservation of 354 service that I'll talk about in a minute, the existing route structure was retained, although it's been shifted as an extension of the Route 80 instead of the 350 via AOA.

525
01:15:02,709 --> 01:15:17,278
So we would still go to Burlington, we would still go to Winchester and Woburn and Arlington, but it will be as the Route 80 to Davis and Bedford-Tufts Green Line extension instead of to Alewife on the Red Line.

526
01:15:20,242 --> 01:15:21,783
bus route 354.

527
01:15:23,103 --> 01:15:29,265
From the northern suburbs, this is probably the biggest change that we've made.

528
01:15:30,066 --> 01:15:38,229
We'd heard a lot of feedback that our initial proposal did not have any express service to Burlington, Woburn, or Medford.

529
01:15:38,789 --> 01:15:45,551
Instead, we had redrawn service in those neighborhoods to have seven day local service to feed into the red, orange, and or green lines.

530
01:15:46,692 --> 01:15:49,033
But one of the things we'd heard from Medford, Woburn,

531
01:15:50,293 --> 01:15:58,417
Burlington was that the travel times were not competitive and that there was a lot of interest in retaining the direct connection into downtown Boston.

532
01:15:59,137 --> 01:16:07,741
Because of the challenges of parking in the downtown, many folks conveyed that they have a car, but they're most likely to use transit for those downtown-oriented trips where parking is constrained.

533
01:16:08,442 --> 01:16:17,506
So in this revised proposal, the 354 would continue to do what it does today and would serve Burlington, Woburn, and Medford during rush hours on weekdays.

534
01:16:19,240 --> 01:16:39,240
In order to make that work with our resource changes, there were a number of other route changes that I mentioned already to keep us within our hours budget for this change in our vehicles and our operator camps.

535
01:16:42,408 --> 01:16:46,609
Then we have one more change, the bus route 54.

536
01:16:47,749 --> 01:16:49,490
There was a route change to this.

537
01:16:49,990 --> 01:16:57,392
It starts in Arlington Center and had originally been proposed to extend over to Riverside and Newton as a crosstown connection.

538
01:16:58,212 --> 01:17:03,833
